==English==

===Etymology===
Of German origin meaning "noble wolf". From Old High German ''adal'' ('[[noble]]') and 
'wolf, wulf'' ('[[wolf]]').

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
#{{given name|male|from Germanic|}} A male [[given name]]. 

